TextToSpeech$Connection$1 is this:

```
        private final ITextToSpeechCallback.Stub mCallback =
                new ITextToSpeechCallback.Stub() {
                    public void onStop(String utteranceId, boolean isStarted)
                            throws RemoteException {
                        UtteranceProgressListener listener = mUtteranceProgressListener;
                        if (listener != null) {
                            listener.onStop(utteranceId, isStarted);
                        }
                    };
```

So what you got here is an IPC call and the other process is keeping the reference to the stub, preventing it from being GCed, and therefore leaking the activity.

Do you want to open a PR on LeakCanary to add this to the list of exclusions?
